<br>
I would try to assess why it didn't work to begin with. Assess where that person is in their life now.. If they've moved on, maybe you should too. Sometimes it's easy to think about being safe and loving someone who you know you can love.. but then you miss out on loving someone who you know can love you back. <br>
<br>
I was stuck in a semi relationship for safety.. he moved on, I didn't.. I blindly loved him, was afraid to not love him. One day I woke up when someone else came into my life that showed that I deserved to be just as happy as my ex was. If I would have spent any more time trying to get the ex to love me, I would have missed out on, quite possibly, the best person to ever have walked into my life.<br>
<br>
Really look at what's going on in both of your lives.. and be realistic in seeing if trying to get her back is worth it.. maybe it's time to let her go and learn to love again.. learn to be loved again. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20525">Shylah</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
